quark_pie_chart.png  Type: Pie chart  
Purpose: Shows the orbital ZBW DP mixing fractions for a representative quark (e.g., up quark, N_k=1 minimal cage).  
Key content:  Three slices labeled 'qDP', 'hDP', 'eDP' (order reversed from lepton to reflect quark preference)  
Colors: likely orange/blue/green or similar palette  
Approximate fractions: ~74% qDP (dominant), with smaller hDP and eDP shares  
Title: something like "Quark Orbital ZBW DP Composition (Up Quark, N_k=1)"

Interpretation: Illustrates the strong qDP preference in quarks due to reversed gradient ordering (qDP lowest energy → most probable). This is the baseline for down-type quarks having additional linear ZBW extras.


